</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1440,1683]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1440,1466]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Vertex pointed and conical in lateral view. Pronotum with a prominent pointed process on anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[203,352,1476,1503]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,182,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-22@33.[151,1436,181,1855]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19. Lichenodraculus species. A–C. L. matti and D–F. L. holgeri. A, D. Male holotype in lateral view. B, E. Head and pronotum. C, F. Cerci in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876259/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs. 19A–B</figureCitation>
), sometimes on posterior margin as well (
<figureCitation box="[823,971,1476,1503]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,182,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-22@33.[151,1436,181,1855]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19. Lichenodraculus species. A–C. L. matti and D–F. L. holgeri. A, D. Male holotype in lateral view. B, E. Head and pronotum. C, F. Cerci in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876259/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs. 19D–E</figureCitation>
). Hind femora and tibiae with cylindrical spines, elongated and curving, all genicular lobes developed as long spines. Male cerci elongate and sickle-shaped or the shape resembling tweezers, internally excavated (
<figureCitation box="[787,933,1548,1575]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,182,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-22@33.[151,1436,181,1855]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19. Lichenodraculus species. A–C. L. matti and D–F. L. holgeri. A, D. Male holotype in lateral view. B, E. Head and pronotum. C, F. Cerci in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876259/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs. 19C, F</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor broad, strongly curved upward, margins parallel and broadly rounded, apex delicately serrate. Female cerci are slender and elongate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1206,1620,1647]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1440,1683]" box="[199,1206,1620,1647]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,1620,1647]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<typeStatus box="[199,258,1621,1647]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Braun, 2011" authorityName="Braun" authorityYear="2011" box="[361,761,1620,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenodraculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matti">
<emphasis box="[361,614,1620,1646]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Lichenodraculus matti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Braun, H." box="[621,761,1621,1647]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="33 - 39" refId="ref38372" refString="Braun, H. (2011) The Little Lichen Dragon - an extraordinary katydid from the Ecuadorian Andes (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae, Phaneropterinae, Dysoniini). Zootaxa, 3032 (1), 33 - 39. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3032.1.3" type="journal article" year="2011">Braun, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by monotypy and original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1440,1683]" box="[199,1033,1656,1683]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1656,1682]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</emphasis>
Ecuadorian Andes and Guiana Shield in 
<collectingCountry box="[813,928,1656,1682]" name="Venezuela" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(Map 4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,990,848,872]" box="[151,990,848,872]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,227,848,872]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Map 4.</emphasis>
Distribution map of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Karsch" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[440,684,848,872]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Apolinaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hygracantha">
<emphasis box="[440,684,848,872]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Apolinaria hygracantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[733,990,848,872]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenodraculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[733,903,848,872]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Lichenodraculus</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,571,953,980]" box="[151,571,953,980]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,571,953,980]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Key to species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braun" authorityYear="2011" box="[366,571,953,980]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenodraculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[366,571,953,980]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Lichenodraculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<keyStep pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<key pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1023,1221]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<keyLead pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
1. Only prozonal spine of the pronotum developed and as long as the vertex (
<figureCitation box="[938,1063,1023,1045]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,182,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-22@33.[151,1436,181,1855]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19. Lichenodraculus species. A–C. L. matti and D–F. L. holgeri. A, D. Male holotype in lateral view. B, E. Head and pronotum. C, F. Cerci in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876259/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs. 19A, B</figureCitation>
); male cerci with inner branch reduced (
<figureCitation box="[233,321,1052,1074]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,182,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-22@33.[151,1436,181,1855]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19. Lichenodraculus species. A–C. L. matti and D–F. L. holgeri. A, D. Male holotype in lateral view. B, E. Head and pronotum. C, F. Cerci in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876259/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 19C</figureCitation>
); ovipositor of female robust, with the dorsal and ventral margins slightly denticulate from the middle to the apex.................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Braun, 2011" authorityName="Braun" authorityYear="2011" box="[1229,1433,1081,1103]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenodraculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matti">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1229,1307,1081,1103]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">L. matti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Braun, H." box="[1312,1433,1082,1103]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="33 - 39" refId="ref38372" refString="Braun, H. (2011) The Little Lichen Dragon - an extraordinary katydid from the Ecuadorian Andes (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae, Phaneropterinae, Dysoniini). Zootaxa, 3032 (1), 33 - 39. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3032.1.3" type="journal article" year="2011">Braun, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1023,1221]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<keyLead pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
- Both prozonal and metazonal spine of the pronotum developed, of similar size and not longer than the vertex in male, in female the pronotal spines are almost as long as the vertex (
<figureCitation box="[729,846,1140,1162]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,182,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-22@33.[151,1436,181,1855]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19. Lichenodraculus species. A–C. L. matti and D–F. L. holgeri. A, D. Male holotype in lateral view. B, E. Head and pronotum. C, F. Cerci in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876259/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 19D, E</figureCitation>
); male cerci with inner branch almost as long as outer branch and with sclerotized margin (
<figureCitation box="[506,591,1170,1192]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,182,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-22@33.[151,1436,181,1855]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19. Lichenodraculus species. A–C. L. matti and D–F. L. holgeri. A, D. Male holotype in lateral view. B, E. Head and pronotum. C, F. Cerci in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876259/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 19F</figureCitation>
); ovipositor slender, dorsal and ventral margins crenulated from middle to apex............................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castaneda, 2013" authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda" authorityYear="2013" box="[1094,1436,1198,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenodraculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holgeri">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1094,1192,1198,1220]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">L. holgeri</emphasis>
Cadena-Castañeda, 2013
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</key>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
